# Walkthrough: Automated App Versioning

I have implemented an automated versioning system that stamps the application with a unique ID (Timestamp + Git Hash) every time you deploy.

## Changes Made

### 1. Deployment Pipeline
Modified [deploy-v2.ps1](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/deploy-v2.ps1) to inject a dynamic metadata step:
- **Automatic Metadata**: Generates `src/version.json` during the build process.
- **Traceability**: Captures the current Git short-hash and a formatted timestamp.

### 2. Login Page UI
Updated [Login.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/pages/Login.tsx) with branded version info:
- **Discreet Placement**: Added to the footer below the copyright.
- **Modern Styling**: Uses a mono-spaced font in a capsule pill for a "technical but clean" look.

### 3. Dashboard Sidebar
Updated [Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx) for supportability:
- **Visible build info**: Tucked away at the very bottom of the sidebar.
- **High-contrast text**: Uses the existing dashboard color palette with low-opacity metadata labels.

## Verification Results

### Build Test (Dry Run)
I ran `.\ship.ps1 -DryRun -SkipConfirm` and verified the following output:
> `-> Generating version metadata (src/version.json)...`
> `[OK] Version info staged: v20260414-0928 (d2cf008)`

### Local Dev Verification
The `src/version.json` placeholder was created to ensure your local dev environment remains functional and shows `vDev-Local`.

---
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The version only updates when you run the **Ship** or **Deploy** scripts. Local development will always show `vDev-Local`.
